𝗔𝘀𝗰𝗲𝗻𝗱 𝙞𝙣𝙞𝙩𝙞𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙫𝙚, 𝙀𝙙𝙪𝙘𝙖𝙧𝙚 𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙒𝙤𝙢𝙚𝙣 𝙞𝙣 𝙏𝙚𝙘𝙝—𝙖 𝙨𝙞𝙭-𝙢𝙤𝙣𝙩𝙝 𝙢𝙚𝙣𝙩𝙤𝙧𝙨𝙝𝙞𝙥 𝙥𝙧𝙤𝙜𝙧𝙖𝙢 

Through this program, students will participate in an exclusive educational experience designed to enhance their skills in areas ranging from coding and software development to holistic professional development. Women in undergraduate engineering courses will also be offered an opportunity to learn from experienced knowledgeable leaders with a diversity of background and perspective. ✨

📚𝘾𝙤𝙪𝙧𝙨𝙚 𝙎𝙩𝙧𝙪𝙘𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙚:

🔹Courses will be held over the weekends. Each tech course includes six contact hours delivered by mentors over three weekends, and each non-tech course includes two contact hours delivered over one weekend.

🔹Learning and networking events would be conducted over weekdays, totalling two to four hours each month.

🔹A dedicated mentor will be assigned throughout the duration of the program for each study group comprising no more than four students.

🔹There will be two cohorts, one each for 2nd and 3rd year students, with up to 40 candidates in each cohort.

🔰 𝙀𝙡𝙞𝙜𝙞𝙗𝙞𝙡𝙞𝙩𝙮:

🔸Candidates must submit an online application that includes the following:

▪️Shortlisted candidates will then undertake an online test that will cover general aptitude as well as basic programming questions.

▪️Students shortlisted from the above step will be interviewed for final selection.

🔸A resume or CV that includes the candidate’s GPA, course of study, and any record of achievement or distinction.

🔸A self-nomination in which the candidates describe their interest in the opportunity and/or what makes them a compelling applicant (300 words or less).
 

📝 𝗔𝗣𝗣𝗟𝗬 𝗕𝗘𝗙𝗢𝗥𝗘 𝟯𝟬𝘁𝗵 𝗔𝗨𝗚𝗨𝗦𝗧, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟭

